overview: The user's intent was to enhance their "Sleep Questionnaire
  Application" by adding persistent data storage and a client-accessible
  dashboard. The approach involved integrating a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB)
  using Prisma, defining a schema for questionnaire responses, and developing
  API endpoints for data interaction. A key decision was to implement a simple
  password-based authentication system for the admin dashboard, which was later
  refined to leverage Next.js middleware for cleaner route protection. The
  outcome is a fully functional backend for data storage and retrieval,
  complemented by an admin interface, ready for testing and deployment.
